<item>
            <title>[PIG-378] FOREACH followed by LIMIT produces wrong results</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-378</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Script:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;grunt&amp;gt; A = load &apos;/user/pig/tests/data/singlefile/studenttab10k&apos; as (name, age, gpa);&lt;br/&gt;
grunt&amp;gt; B = foreach A generate name;&lt;br/&gt;
grunt&amp;gt; C = limit B 10;&lt;br/&gt;
grunt&amp;gt; dump C;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Output:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;((luke king,65,0.73))&lt;br/&gt;
((fred miller,55,3.77))&lt;br/&gt;
((holly white,43,0.24))&lt;br/&gt;
((calvin brown,56,0.72))&lt;br/&gt;
((katie carson,25,3.65))&lt;br/&gt;
((holly davidson,57,2.43))&lt;br/&gt;
((holly davidson,59,1.26))&lt;br/&gt;
((luke steinbeck,51,1.14))&lt;br/&gt;
((nick underhill,31,2.46))&lt;br/&gt;
((ulysses thompson,64,1.90))&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that we have a tuple with 3 fields within tuple&lt;/p&gt;</description>
